{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900950317,"sessionID":"ses_2840e4a57ffeD9yjtzaPsmhTe7","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf1fb35001R3pxOFLqsWTmlr","messageID":"msg_d7bf1d2f5001LdsF74i5WLE9p3","sessionID":"ses_2840e4a57ffeD9yjtzaPsmhTe7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a4f087c0df4d42bf9690d575580fa46b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: from typing import Optional\n2: \n3: \n4: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n5:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n6: \n7:     pass\n8: \n9: \n10: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n11:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n12: \n13:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None) -> None:\n14:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n15:         self.stderr = stderr\n16:         self.command = command\n17:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n18: \n19: \n20: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n21:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\"\"\"\n22: \n23:     pass\n24: \n25: \n26: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n27:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\"\"\"\n28: \n29:     pass\n30: \n31: \n32: __all__ = [\n33:     \"AgentCubeError\",\n34:     \"CommandExecutionError\",\n35:     \"SessionError\",\n36:     \"DataPlaneError\",\n37: ]\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"from typing import Optional\n\n\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n\n    pass\n\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None) -> None:\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py","time":{"start":1775900950293,"end":1775900950316}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900950321,"sessionID":"ses_2840e4a57ffeD9yjtzaPsmhTe7","part":{"id":"prt_d7bf1f33f001zvQh2Jzim9gRRr","messageID":"msg_d7bf1d2f5001LdsF74i5WLE9p3","sessionID":"ses_2840e4a57ffeD9yjtzaPsmhTe7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b830ac1735e3465fb698efd2fd91e768","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK Tests — Design\n2: \n3: AR: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n4: Module: sdk-python/tests\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ## Architecture\n9: \n10: ### Test Structure\n11: \n12: | File | Module Tested | Focus |\n13: |------|---------------|-------|\n14: | `test_code_interpreter.py` | `agentcube.code_interpreter` | `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle, delegation |\n15: | `test_control_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.control_plane` | `ControlPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n16: | `test_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.code_interpreter_data_plane` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` API calls |\n17: | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle, invoke |\n18: | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n19: | `test_agent_runtime_integration.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | Full workflow integration tests |\n20: | `test_exceptions.py` | `agentcube.exceptions` | Exception hierarchy validation |\n21: | `test_utils.py` | `agentcube.utils.*` | Utility functions |\n22: | `test_exports.py` | `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Public API surface validation |\n23: \n24: ### Test Categories\n25: \n26: 1. **Unit Tests** — Mock HTTP responses, test single class/method behavior\n27: 2. **Integration Tests** — Test component interactions with mock backend\n28: 3. **Contract Tests** — Verify HTTP request/response format matches spec\n29: \n30: ### Mocking Strategy\n31: \n32: - `responses` library for HTTP mocking (wire-level interception)\n33: - `unittest.mock` for patching internal dependencies\n34: - `pytest-mock` for fixture-based mock injection\n35: - `MagicMock` for response objects when testing client internals\n36: \n37: ## Data Structures\n38: \n39: ### Mock Response Data\n40: \n41: #### Control Plane Responses\n42: \n43: ```python\n44: # create_session success\n45: {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n46: \n47: # create_session failure (missing sessionId)\n48: {}\n49: \n50: # delete_session success\n51: # HTTP 200 or 404 (both treated as success)\n52: ```\n53: \n54: #### Code Interpreter Data Plane Responses\n55: \n56: ```python\n57: # execute_command success\n58: {\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"}\n59: \n60: # execute_command failure\n61: {\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error message\"}\n62: \n63: # list_files\n64: {\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n65: ```\n66: \n67: #### Agent Runtime Responses\n68: \n69: ```python\n70: # bootstrap (GET) — headers only\n71: # Response headers: {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n72: \n73: # invoke (POST)\n74: {\"result\": \"success\"}\n75: {\"output\": \"processed\", \"status\": \"completed\"}\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Test Fixtures\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: # tmp_path fixture (pytest built-in) for file operations\n82: local_file = tmp_path / \"test.txt\"\n83: local_file.write_text(\"content\")\n84: \n85: # Environment isolation\n86: os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = \"http://router\"\n87: os.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = \"http://wm\"\n88: # Cleanup after test\n89: del os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"]\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## API Contracts\n93: \n94: ### Control Plane Client Tests (`test_control_plane.py`)\n95: \n96: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n97: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n98: | `TestControlPlaneClientInit` | Default/custom timeout | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` defaults |\n99: | `TestAuthTokenResolution` | Explicit/file/env | Token resolution order: arg → file → none |\n100: | `TestURLResolution` | Explicit/env/required | URL resolution order: arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` → raise |\n101: | `TestCreateSession` | Success/missing ID/metadata | `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, JSON body format |\n102: | `TestDeleteSession` | Success/404/failure | `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`, 404 = success |\n103: | `TestClose` | Session cleanup | `session.close()` called |\n104: \n105: ### Code Interpreter Data Plane Tests (`test_data_plane.py`)\n106: \n107: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n108: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n109: | `TestDataPlaneClientInit` | session_id/base_url/params | Constructor parameter requirements |\n110: | `TestSessionHeader` | Header lowercase | `x-agentcube-session-id` header on session |\n111: | `TestBaseURLConstruction` | URL from router | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr}/invocations/` |\n112: | `TestExecuteCommand` | Success/list input/timeout buffer | `POST api/execute`, JSON body, timeout+2s buffer |\n113: | `TestWriteFile` | base64/mode | `POST api/files`, base64 content, `\"0644\"` mode |\n114: | `TestUploadFile` | multipart/session header | `POST api/files` multipart, explicit session header |\n115: | `TestDownloadFile` | stream/parent dir/slash strip | `GET api/files/{path}`, `stream=True`, leading slash removal |\n116: | `TestListFiles` | query/default path | `GET api/files`, `params={\"path\": ...}` |\n117: \n118: ### Code Interpreter Client Tests (`test_code_interpreter.py`)\n119: \n120: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n121: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n122: | `TestCodeInterpreterClientInit` | URL required/env/explicit | `ROUTER_URL` env or arg required |\n123: | `TestSessionCreation` | Created/reused | `create_session` called when no `session_id` |\n124: | `TestContextManager` | Normal exit/exception | `__exit__` calls `stop()` always |\n125: | `TestStopMethod` | Cleanup/conditional delete | Data plane close, control plane delete only if created |\n126: | `TestExecuteCommandDelegation` | Pass-through | `execute_command` delegates to `_dp_client` |\n127: | `TestRunCode` | Python language | Write `.py` file, execute `python3 <file>` |\n128: | `TestFileOperations` | write/list | Delegation to data plane methods |\n129: | `TestVerboseMode` | Logger level | `DEBUG` when verbose, `INFO` otherwise |\n130: | `TestDataPlaneInitFailure` | Cleanup on failure | `delete_session` called if data plane init fails |\n131: \n132: ### Agent Runtime Client Tests (`test_agent_runtime_client.py`)\n133: \n134: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n135: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n136: | `TestAgentRuntimeClientInit` | All params | Parameter storage |\n137: | `TestRouterURLRequired` | Required validation | `ROUTER_URL` or arg required |\n138: | `TestRouterURLResolution` | Env/explicit | Resolution order |\n139: | `TestSessionReuse` | Provided session_id | No bootstrap GET when `session_id` provided |\n140: | `TestSessionBootstrap` | GET bootstrap | `GET` base invocation URL for session header |\n141: | `TestDataPlaneInit` | dp_client creation | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instantiated |\n142: | `TestContextManager` | enter/exit/exception | `close()` called on exit |\n143: | `TestInvoke` | delegation/without session | `dp_client.invoke` called, error if no session |\n144: | `TestClose` | data plane close | `dp_client.close()` called |\n145: \n146: ### Agent Runtime Data Plane Tests (`test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n147: \n148: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n149: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n150: | `TestDataPlaneClientInit` | Default/custom timeout | Timeout defaults |\n151: | `TestSessionHeaderConstant` | Value check | `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n152: | `TestBaseURLConstruction` | URL format | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` |\n153: | `TestConnectionPooling` | HTTPAdapter | `HTTPAdapter` mounted for http/https |\n154: | `TestBootstrapSessionID` | success/missing header | `GET` base URL, header extraction, error if missing |\n155: | `TestInvoke` | with session | `POST` base URL, JSON body |\n156: | `TestInvokeHeaders` | headers correctness | `x-agentcube-session-id` + `Content-Type: application/json` |\n157: | `TestInvokeTimeout` | override/default | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple |\n158: \n159: ### Integration Tests (`test_agent_runtime_integration.py`)\n160: \n161: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n162: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n163: | `TestSessionLifecycle` | Full workflow | Bootstrap → invoke → close |\n164: | `TestInvokeWorkflow` | Payload processing | POST with payload, response parsing |\n165: | `TestSessionReuseIntegration` | Multiple invokes | Same session across multiple calls |\n166: | `TestBootstrapFailure` | Missing header error | ValueError raised |\n167: | `TestInvokeFailure` | HTTP error | `requests.HTTPError` raised |\n168: \n169: ### Utils Tests (`test_utils.py`)\n170: \n171: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n172: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n173: | `TestCreateSession` | Returns/adapters/custom pool | `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` |\n174: | `TestReadTokenFromFile` | success/not found/strip/multiline | File read, strip, empty on missing |\n175: | `TestGetLogger` | Returns/default level/custom level | `logging.Logger`, `INFO` default, level config |\n176: \n177: ### Exception Tests (`test_exceptions.py`)\n178: \n179: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n180: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n181: | `TestExceptionHierarchy` | Inheritance | All inherit from `AgentCubeError` |\n182: | `TestCommandExecutionError` | Constructor/message | `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`, message format |\n183: | `TestSessionError` | Docstring/inheritance | Docstring contains \"session\" |\n184: | `TestDataPlaneError` | Docstring/inheritance | Docstring contains \"data plane\" |\n185: \n186: ### Export Tests (`test_exports.py`)\n187: \n188: | Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n189: |------------|----------|-------------------|\n190: | `TestRootPackageExports` | Import/`__all__` | Only `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n191: | `TestClientsPackageExports` | Import/`__all__` | `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n192: \n193: ## Error Handling\n194: \n195: ### Exception Types Tested\n196: \n197: | Exception | Raised When | Test Coverage |\n198: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n199: | `ValueError` | Missing required config (router_url, workload_manager_url, sessionId) | All client init tests |\n200: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command non-zero exit | `test_data_plane.py::TestExecuteCommand::test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` |\n201: | `FileNotFoundError` | Upload local file not found | `test_data_plane.py::TestUploadFile::test_upload_file_not_found` |\n202: | `requests.HTTPError` | HTTP failure (non-2xx) | Integration tests with `status=500` |\n203: | `RuntimeError` | Data plane client not initialized | `CodeInterpreterClient` methods |\n204: \n205: ### Error Message Patterns\n206: \n207: ```python\n208: # Config errors\n209: \"router_url must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n210: \"workload_manager_url must be provided via argument or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n211: \"sessionId not found in create_session response\"\n212: \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n213: \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n214: \n215: # Execution errors\n216: \"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n217: \"Unsupported language: {language}. Supported: python, py, python3\"\n218: \"Either base_url or router_url, namespace, and cr_name must be provided\"\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ## Testing Strategy\n222: \n223: ### Test Pyramid\n224: \n225: ```\n226:      ┌─────────────┐\n227:      │ Integration │  ← test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n228:      │    (6)      │     Full workflow with mock backend\n229:      ├─────────────┤\n230:      │   Contract  │  ← HTTP request/response format tests\n231:      │    (15)     │     within each test file\n232:      ├─────────────┤\n233:      │    Unit     │  ← Most tests (mocked internals)\n234:      │   (100+)    │     Isolated class/method tests\n235:      └─────────────┘\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Mock Levels\n239: \n240: 1. **Wire-level** — `responses` intercepts actual HTTP calls\n241:    - Used for: HTTP contract tests, integration tests\n242:    - Example: `responses.post(\"http://wm/v1/code-interpreter\", json={\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"})`\n243: \n244: 2. **Object-level** — `MagicMock` replaces response objects\n245:    - Used for: Testing client internals without HTTP\n246:    - Example: `mock_response.json.return_value = {\"exit_code\": 0}`\n247: \n248: 3. **Dependency-level** — `patch` replaces entire classes\n249:    - Used for: Testing failure paths, cleanup behavior\n250:    - Example: `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client)`\n251: \n252: ### Coverage Goals\n253: \n254: | Module | Target Coverage | Current Tests |\n255: |--------|-----------------|---------------|\n256: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | 100% (exports only) | `test_exports.py` |\n257: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | 95%+ | `test_code_interpreter.py` (296 lines) |\n258: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | 95%+ | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` + `test_agent_runtime_integration.py` |\n259: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_control_plane.py` (169 lines) |\n260: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_data_plane.py` (338 lines) |\n261: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` (178 lines) |\n262: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | 100% | `test_exceptions.py` (66 lines) |\n263: | `agentcube/utils/*.py` | 95%+ | `test_utils.py` (71 lines) |\n264: \n265: ### Test Execution\n266: \n267: ```bash\n268: # Run all tests\n269: pytest sdk-python/tests/ -v\n270: \n271: # Run with coverage\n272: pytest sdk-python/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n273: \n274: # Run specific module\n275: pytest sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n276: \n277: # Run specific test\n278: pytest sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestContextManager::test_context_manager_calls_stop\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### CI Integration\n282: \n283: - `pytest.ini_options` configured in `pyproject.toml`\n284: - `addopts = \"-v --tb=short\"` for verbose output with short traceback\n285: - Coverage excludes: `pragma: no cover`, `__repr__`, `NotImplementedError`, `__main__`\n286: \n287: ### Key Test Patterns\n288: \n289: 1. **Parameter Validation**\n290:    ```python\n291:    def test_router_url_required(self) -> None:\n292:        if \"ROUTER_URL\" in os.environ:\n293:            del os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"]\n294:        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n295:            CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n296:    ```\n297: \n298: 2. **Delegation Testing**\n299:    ```python\n300:    def test_execute_command_delegates_to_data_plane(self) -> None:\n301:        # Setup mock response\n302:        responses.post(..., json={\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"})\n303:        client = CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n304:        result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n305:        assert result == \"output\"\n306:    ```\n307: \n308: 3. **Cleanup Verification**\n309:    ```python\n310:    def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleans_up_session(self) -> None:\n311:        mock_cp_client.delete_session = Mock(return_value=True)\n312:        with patch(...):\n313:            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n314:                CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n315:        mock_cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once_with(\"session-123\")\n316:    ```\n317: \n318: 4. **HTTP Contract Testing**\n319:    ```python\n320:    def test_execute_command_json_body(self) -> None:\n321:        client.execute_command(\"python3 script.py\", timeout=30)\n322:        call_args = client._request.call_args\n323:        body = json.loads(call_args.args[2].decode())\n324:        assert body[\"command\"] == [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n325:        assert body[\"timeout\"] == \"30s\"\n326:    ```\n327: \n328: 5. **Integration Workflow**\n329:    ```python\n330:    @responses.activate\n331:    def test_full_session_lifecycle(self):\n332:        responses.get(..., headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"})\n333:        responses.post(..., json={\"result\": \"success\"})\n334:        with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:\n335:            assert client.session_id == \"session-123\"\n336:            result = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})\n337:            assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n338:    ```\n339: \n340: ## Dependencies\n341: \n342: ```toml\n343: [project.optional-dependencies]\n344: dev = [\n345:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",       # Test framework\n346:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\", # Mock fixtures\n347:     \"pytest-cov>=4.0.0\",   # Coverage plugin\n348:     \"responses>=0.23.0\",   # HTTP mocking\n349: ]\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ## Future Considerations\n353: \n354: 1. **E2E Tests** — Add tests that run against real backend (marked with `@pytest.mark.e2e`)\n355: 2. **Performance Tests** — Add timeout behavior tests with actual delay simulation\n356: 3. **Error Recovery Tests** — Add tests for retry behavior (if implemented)\n357: 4. **Multi-language Tests** — Expand `run_code` tests for additional languages beyond Python\n\n(End of file - total 357 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK Tests — Design\n\nAR: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\nModule: sdk-python/tests\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Test Structure\n\n| File | Module Tested | Focus |\n|------|---------------|-------|\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | `agentcube.code_interpreter` | `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle, delegation |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.control_plane` | `ControlPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.code_interpreter_data_plane` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` API calls |\n| `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle, invoke |\n| `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n| `test_agent_runtime_integration.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | Full workflow integration tests |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | `agentcube.exceptions` | Exception hierarchy validation |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md","time":{"start":1775900950288,"end":1775900950318}}}}
